
 TODO: write me!

 For package building see the 'Docs/packaging-howto' file.


1/
	./configure [ option ]

	where basic options:

		--prefix=DIR
			Install path prefix. Default /usr/local/

		--with-model=MODEL
			The mobil phone model (This is now only used as a
			default if ~/.gnokiirc cannot be read.):

				6110	- for Nokia 6110/5110 
				3810	- for Nokia 3810 (default)	
		
		--with-port=PORT
			Serial port for communication:

				/dev/ttyS0	Linux "COM1" (default)
				/dev/ttyS1	Linux "COM2"
				/dev/ttyd0	FreeBSD
				COM1		MS-Window COM1

		--without-x
			Compile without GTK (Xwin) programs
		
		--disable-nls
			Set if you don't have/want GNU gettext support
		
		--enable-security
			Set if you want to enable all security features

		--enable-debug
			Set if you want debug code. in gnokii

		--help		
			show all options


	Good default (example):

		./configure --prefix=/usr \
			    --enable-gettext \
			    --with-port=/dev/ttyS1 \
			    --with-model=6110 

2/
	compilation:
	
		make 
		(make dep - if you want/need) 
		make install
		make install-docs

	clean source:
	
		make clean	 - standard clean
		make distclean   - clean all ./configure outputs
				   (after this command you must run
				    ./configure again if you need use
                                    any Makefile)
